{"message":"Certainly! I hold a Bachelor of Music Education from the University of Cincinnati and currently teach music at Roosevelt Elementary (part of Cincinnati Public Schools). I perform regularly as part of The Willow Street Folk Duo, focusing on Appalachian and folk music. Our performances include monthly gigs at the downtown farmers market and appearances at events like the Cincinnati Summer Music Fest.

Additionally, I have experience leading community music workshops for young children, incorporating audience participation and musical storytelling. Returning to performing after a medical leave for postpartum depression was a key part of my recovery, and continuing these public and community-oriented performances is very meaningful to me.

If you need any details about specific events or other aspects of my music experience, I’d be happy to provide them!"}

